=== RAW MODEL ANSWER ===
Answer: Step 1: Use 4-chloro-5-methyl-3-ethyl-1-ethyl-1H-pyrazolo[3,4-b]pyridine as the heterobicyclic core and perform benzylic bromination (NBS, AIBN) to give 4-chloro-5-(bromomethyl)-3-ethyl-1-ethyl-1H-pyrazolo[3,4-b]pyridine. | Step 2: Displace the 4-chloro group by SNAr with tetrahydropyran-4-ylamine to form 5-(bromomethyl)-3-ethyl-1-ethyl-4-[(tetrahydropyran-4-yl)amino]-1H-pyrazolo[3,4-b]pyridine. | Step 3: Convert the bromomethyl group into the aminomethyl handle via Gabriel substitution (K phthalimide) then hydrazinolysis, giving 5-(aminomethyl)-3-ethyl-1-ethyl-4-[(tetrahydropyran-4-yl)amino]-1H-pyrazolo[3,4-b]pyridine. | Step 4: In parallel, open succinic anhydride with 3-bromo-4-chlorobenzylamine to obtain 4-oxo-4-[(3-bromo-4-chlorobenzyl)amino]butanoic acid. | Step 5: Couple the Step 3 aminomethyl heterocycle with the Step 4 acid (HATU or EDCI, base) to furnish CCc1nc2c(cnn2CC)c(NC2CCOCC2)c1CNC(=O)CCC(=O)NCc1ccc(Cl)c(Br)c1.

